ation2\" />\n* Suite for violin and piano, Op.&nbsp;28 (1962)<ref name=\"Foundation2\" /><ref>{{cite web | title=Library of Congress \u2013 Zografski, Tomislav |url=http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no88003831|website=www.loc.gov|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref>\n* ''Scripts'' for baritone and piano, Op.&nbsp;39 (1963)<ref name=\"Ohrid1\" />\n* ''Fantasia corale'' (1967)<ref name=\"GroveMusic1\" /><ref>{{cite web | title=Fantasia corale \u2013 SearchWorks catalog |url=https://searchworks.stanford.edu/view/289836|website=www.searchworks.stanford.edu|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n* String Quartet, Op.&nbsp;58 (1968)\n* Sonatina in C for two pianos, Op.&nbsp;142 (1969)<ref name=\"Musicological1\" />\n* ''In praise of Cyril and Methodius'' (1969)<ref name=\"Foundation1\" /><ref>{{cite web | title=Stanford University Libraries \u2014 Opening Night! Opera & Oratorio Premieres |url=http://operadata.stanford.edu/catalog/10203438|website=www.stanford.edu|access-date=2020-01-28}}</ref>\n* ''Cantus Coronatus'' (1969)<ref>{{cite book |last=Samson |first=Jim |date=2013 |title=Music in the Balkans |url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=yJ60SHL4R-0C&lpg=PR4&pg=PR4#v=onepage&q&f=false |location=Boston |publisher=Koninklijke Brill|page=491 |isbn=9789004250376}}</ref>\n* ''Siyaniem for soloist and mixed choir'', Op.&nbsp;74 (1972)<ref>{{cite AV media |people=Chamber Choir of the Feliks Nowowiejski Academy of Music |date=29 August 2017 |title=OCF: AWARD \u2033Tomislav Zografski\u2033 |language=Macedonian |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ao3ik2CuXdw |access-date=1 April 2020 |format= Video |location=Diamond Hall of Hotel Inex, Ohrid, Republic of Macedonia |publisher=YouTube}}</ref>\n* ''Allegro barrocco'' for two violins and piano (1973)<ref>{{cite web | title=Review of Composers \u2013 Composers' Association of Serbia |url=http://composers.rs/en/?page_id=994|website=www.composers.rs|access-date=2020-01-22}}</ref>\n* Passacaglia, symphonic poem (1981)<ref name=\"Foundation1\" /